This is not a five star hotel but you are not paying five star prices and as stated above the location is awesome.	We're the sort of travelers who aren't interested in luxury and a lot of amenities with our accommodations.	It features a children's carnival, which is great for families, but not very appealing to business travelers.	We had a great room at the end of the hall with a king size bed, and a connecting door to a smaller room with two doubles.	Our room was most comfortable and with its amenities, left nothing to be desired This is simply a first class hotel.